Hey! I am Praveen Venkatesh from Indian Institute of Technology Gandhinagar

  • Current MITACS Globalink Research Intern at Western University, Canada

  • Passionate about perception in robots, and applied deep learning

  • Love tinkering around with electronics and experimenting with crazy ideas. Check my projects out here: Projects


I am a senior undergrad student in Electrical Engineering at IIT Gandhinagar, specializing in Robotics. In my spare time, I engage myself in tinkering with electronics and automating my life. I have always firmly believed that we should strive to be the best version of ourselves, and have transformed significantly as a person during my time at IITGN. Over the course of three years at the institute, I have been part of several student-run groups and developmental projects, and have actively contributed towards improving the sporting and technical culture at the institute.

Some quirky things about me:

    • I can solve the 3x3 cube in around 13 seconds and can solve 14 different twisty puzzle derivatives of the 3x3 (Including solving it blindfolded!). Check my World Cubing Association profile here: Praveen Venkatesh | World Cube Association

    • I go on typeracer and have fun when I feel like it. Its how I can type at 95+ WPM :P

    • Music = ❤️

    • I can play the Keyboard, and can play a few tunes on the flute.

    • I can Yodel! (Although people find yodelling irritating 😜)
